      "content": "<bpt id=\"p11\">**</bpt>HDInsight on Linux<ept id=\"p11\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph8\"/> - Azure HDInsight provides the option of creating Hadoop clusters that run on Linux (Ubuntu) virtual machines (VMs). You can use this option if you are familiar with Linux or Unix, are migrating from an existing Linux-based Hadoop solution, or want easy integration with Hadoop ecosystem components built for Linux. You can create an HDInsight cluster on Linux from a client computer running Windows or Linux by using the Azure Portal, the Azure CLI, or the HDInsight .NET SDK (Windows only).",
